        <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="Description">
          <title>Description</title>
          <p>The specimen was identified using <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B141162">Bouček (1988)</xref>, and references listed therein. I recommend that <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Scutellista</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">caerulea</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> be added to the New Zealand Organisms Register (NZOR) as exotic, present in the wild. It is unclear if the new specimen represents a descendant of the original stock released in Nelson in 1921, or a new incursion from overseas. The balance of evidence favours the latter hypothesis, since Auckland is far from Nelson, and the species has not been seen in N.Z. for nearly a century.</p>
        </tp:treatment-sec>
